<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,656,972]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,692,719]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Distribution.</emphasis>
Thus far only recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[689,753,693,719]" name="Spain" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Spain</collectingCountry>
and North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[967,1066,693,719]" name="Portugal" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one province (Douro Litoral) in this study, and Algarve (Dyte unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,656,972]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,765,791]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Ecology.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[336,434,765,791]" name="Portugal" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, this species has been collected in fair numbers in agricultural land (with greenhouses) on sandy soil, and in an area with a mosaic of habitats from dunes to forest, riparian corridors and agricultural fields; one specimen was retrieved from a sandy spit at the mouth of the river Douro. Its ecology in the rest of its distribution range is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,656,972]" box="[199,456,908,935]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,908,935]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
